                                <li>The fifth and final column contains the relative minor key. Relative minor keys are always a minor 3rd below the Root note (or Do) of the major key signature. The relative minor has the same notatino on the key signature and grand staff, as well as the same altered notes when using natural minor.</li>
                            </ul>
