                    <h3 class="title">The Circle of Fifths</h3>
                    <p class="subtitle">The circle of fifths is a pattern that will help you in nearly every aspect of music theory.</p>
                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Going clockwise around the circle of fifths, the interval is a P5 between each section.</li>
                            <li>Going counterclockwise around the circle of fifths, the interval is a P4 between each section.</li>
                            <li>The outer ring is Major keys, and the inner ring is Minor keys. The Major keys are lined up with their relative minor.</li>
                            <li>Starting at C, then going clockwise around the circle of fifths shows the order of the sharp keys. (C is 0 sharps, G is 1 sharp, D is 2 sharps, etc.)</li>
                            <li>Starting at C, then going counterclockwise around the circle of fifths shows the order of the flat keys. (C is 0 flats, F is 1 flat, B♭ is 2 flats, etc.)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
